{"key":"processedPost-12328452","value":{"id":12328452,"first":12327900,"last":12337403,"when":1270401616,"utime":"04/04/10 08:20 PM","content":"Perlite in a shotgun terrarium will not dry out.&nbsp; This is because when you mist the cakes, the overspray replaces what has evaporated from the perlite in order to provide humidity.<br /><br />You don't cut back on FAE to maintain humidity.&nbsp; If FAE causes a loss in humidity, you mist more.&nbsp; Four to five air exchanges per hour are recommended.&nbsp; A properly made and set up shotgun terrarium performs this level of air exchange automatically.<br />RR","title":"Re: Maintaining Humidity?"}}